<subSubSection id="B73727B3BC7E7905F197F16A78FA2DE0" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="CA6CDCA4D36655EBFF5999B964688191" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C4009E7DEAFF763F9B3FBC25DC123281" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
A local and range-restricted species shared between NE Greece and south Bulgaria. In Greece, it has been reported from the mountains of Athos, Pangeo, Orvilos, Menikio and Falakro, all belonging to the NE floristic region (
<bibRefCitation id="CEC682DB17CF60E6BC2332CAB5885180" author="Hartvig, P." journalOrPublisher="Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668771" refString="Hartvig, P., 1991. Mountain Flora of Greece 2. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh" title="Mountain Flora of Greece 2" year="1991">Hartvig 1991</bibRefCitation>
). The new locality on Mt. Achladovouno extends the distribution range of the species to the east.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
